The equation \(x^{\log y} = y^{\log x}\) holds for all positive \(x\) and \(y\) because taking logs of both sides gives \(\log y \cdot \log x = \log x \cdot \log y\), which is always true.  
Thus, the graph is the set of all points where \(x > 0\) and \(y > 0\), which is the open first quadrant.  

